  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Some users have reported intermittent periods of time where no slot events are seen for a period of time.\n\nThe current reported cases we're working through have all been using data-storage-mode minimal.\n\nOne occasion coincides with having high `p2p-peer-upper-bound` set, and reducing to 128 has been successful in stopping the freeze from happening.\n\nWe're gathering information currently around these freezes, so if you do see them please feel free to submit here with any custom options you may be using, the version of teku you're using, any log file activity that may happen during that period of time.",
